net.openhft.chronicle.engine.map

Class FilePerKeyValueStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.openhft.chronicle.engine.map.FilePerKeyValueStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, java.util.function.Consumer<EngineReplication.ReplicationEntry>, KeyValueStore<String,net.openhft.chronicle.bytes.BytesStore>, StringBytesStoreKeyValueStore, SubscriptionKeyValueStore<String,net.openhft.chronicle.bytes.BytesStore>, Assetted<KeyValueStore<String,net.openhft.chronicle.bytes.BytesStore>>, KeyedView, AuthenticatedKeyValueStore<String,net.openhft.chronicle.bytes.BytesStore>

    public class FilePerKeyValueStore
extends Object
implements StringBytesStoreKeyValueStore, net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.Closeable
    A Map implementation that stores each entry as a file in a directory. The key is the file fullName and the value is the contents of the file.

    The class is effectively an abstraction over a directory in the file system. Therefore when the underlying files are changed an event will be fired to those registered for notifications.

    Updates will be fired every time the file is saved but will be suppressed if the value has not changed. To avoid temporary files (e.g. if edited in vi) being included in the map, any file starting with a '.' will be ignored.

    Note the WatchService is extremely OS dependant. Mas OSX registers very few events if they are done quickly and there is a significant delay between the event and the event being triggered.
